{start_of_verse}
{start_of_verse}
      [CM7]           [Dm7]           [Em7]            [FM7]          [Am7]
I was fine with the men who would come into your life now and again.

      [Dm9]           [D7]                    [FM7]    [G7]           [CM7]  [CmM7]
I was fine 'cause I knew that they didn't really matter until you.

      [CM7]           [Dm7]         [Em7]                [FM7]            [Am7]
I was fine when you came and we fought like it was all some silly game

     [Dm7]            [D7]           [FM7]               [G7]                [CM7]
over her; who she'd chose. After all those years I never thought I'd lose.


{start_of_chorus}
     [CM7]             [Am7]        [Dm9]         [G13]
It's over, isn't it?   Isn't it?   Isn't it over?

     [Em7]             [Am7]         [A7]         [C#dim7]
It's over, isn't it?    Isn't it?   Isn't it over?

    [Dm9]         [G13]                [CM7]                 [Am7]
You won and she chose you, and she loved you and she's gone.

     [Dm9]            [G13]              [CM7]   /C  /B
It's over isn't it? Why can't I move on?


{start_of_bridge}
[Am7]     [E7/B]   [CM7] [Dm9]      [CM7]     [Bdim7]    [Am7] [E7/G#]
War and glory; reinvention; fusion; freedom; her attention.

[Am7]    [E7/B]      [CM7]  [Dm9]      [CM7]      [Bdim7]   [E7/G#]
Out in daylight, my potential, bold, precise, experimental.

[Am]       [AmM7]        [Am7]       [Am6]
